        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-908",
        "content": "Yes, call me by my pet name! let me hear The name I used to run at, when a child, From innocent play, and leave the cowslips plied, To glance up in some face that proved me dear With the look of its eyes.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-low",
